5 â€” Cross-cutting behaviors (detailed)
Primary CTA placement
Primary action is always near thumb reach (bottom full-width button or FAB)
Secondary actions less prominent (text buttons or icon-only)
Progress & timeline
Every multi-step flow shows stepper at top (Step 1 of 3) and progress bars for WOs.
Undo & confirmation
Destructive actions show confirm modals with undo toast (e.g., â€œPO deleted â€” Undoâ€).
Microcopy tone
Plain, supportive, non-technical. Always show consequence of action.
â€œRecord payment? This will reserve materials and trigger production.â€
â€œMark delivered? Customer will be notified by WhatsApp.â€
Localization
Strings stored externally; default English + Gujarati + Hindi. Show small language selector on Profile.
Accessibility
Tap targets >=48dp, high contrast, optional large type mode, voice input labels.

6 â€” Offline-first & sync/conflict strategy (practical)
Local storage
Use local DB (Realm/SQLite) to store entities and pending events.
Sync model
Append-only event queue stored locally; periodic or manual sync.
Sync visual states: Pending (clock icon), Syncing (spinning icon), Synced (green dot).
Conflict resolution:
If clash (two users edit same record), show a simple diff: â€œWe found an edit conflict on Order #. Choose: Your version / Server version / Mergeâ€ with conservative defaults (prefer server for financials; prefer latest for WOs).
Automatic retry with exponential backoff.
File uploads (photos) compressed and queued.
Critical UX
Never block user for offline; allow actions but mark whether theyâ€™re provisional and require sync for cross-user visibility.
For payments: flag with â€œPending verificationâ€ until bank reconciliation or proof accepted.

7 â€” Voice UX (pattern & examples)
Design patterns
Always show transcribed text live and require a short confirmation for critical actions (payments, sales order creation).
Support simple imperative commands and Q&A:
Commands: â€œCreate quote for Suresh Traders, 500m cotton 40s, price 90.â€
Status queries: â€œShow open work orders today.â€
Insight query: â€œAre any shipments delayed?â€
Confirmation flows
For non-critical: voice executes immediately and shows toast.
For critical: voice shows â€œI will create a proforma for â‚¹X â€” approve?â€ (Confirm/Cancel)
Fallback
If voice fails (no internet for ASR), offer typed quick-forms.

