Device + connectivity assumptions & approach
Device reality
Most users do have a smartphone, but phones may be mid-to-low range (Android 7â€“11; 1â€“3 GB RAM). Manufacturers may also have a tablet in the office. Plan for conservative performance and image compression.
Connectivity reality
Many factories have intermittent connectivity. Assume: reads mostly work (cached), writes must be queued & synced.
PWA must be offline-capable for core tasks: create lead, start/stop job, record payment (store proof locally), capture GRN/POD photos (queued).
Design trade-offs
Voice commands are high value but can be â€œonline-enhancedâ€ (i.e., use simple offline dictation or require connectivity for best accuracy). For MVP â€” make voice optional; add later if time permits.
WhatsApp sharing and PDF generation use the browserâ€™s Share API â€” they work only when online or with the app installed.

